data.name: Slow-Braised Pork Shoulder with Rich Gravy and Herb-Infused Mashed Potatoes
data.quickTastyDescription: Tender, slow-braised pork shoulder served with a luscious gravy and creamy herb-infused mashed potatoes.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large Dutch oven, heat some oil over medium-high heat. Season the pork shoulder with salt and pepper, then sear it on all sides until browned. Remove the pork and set aside.
In the same pot, add onions and garlic, sauté until translucent.
Deglaze the pot with red wine, scraping the bottom to release the browned bits.
Add the beef broth, thyme, rosemary, and bay leaves. Bring to a simmer.
Return the pork shoulder to the pot, cover, and transfer to the oven. Braise for 4 hours or until the meat is fork-tender.
For the mashed potatoes, boil the potatoes in salted water until tender, about 15-20 minutes. Drain and return to the pot.
Add butter, cream, salt, and pepper to the potatoes, and mash until creamy. Stir in chopped fresh herbs if desired.
Once the pork is done, remove it from the oven. Let it rest before shredding. Strain the cooking liquid and reduce it in a saucepan to create a gravy.
Serve the shredded pork topped with rich gravy alongside the herb-infused mashed potatoes.
data.detailedName: Slow-Braised Pork Shoulder with Rich Gravy and Herb-Infused Mashed Potatoes
data.modifiersForBase: Slow-braised with rich gravy and served with herb-infused mashed potatoes.
